OPTIMIZATION IDEAS (do ablation studies on some of these later):
1. only do local PSO since its cheaper for SMEM
2. lazy init of PSO, only init when needed
3. move everything to a GPU (paper uses CPU for updating global best and path recomputation, but this is a bottleneck since it requires copying data back and forth)
4. recompute the paths on the fly so that memory bandwidth is not a bottleneck

Future work:
1. Multiple GPU support 
2. Cutlass for more control over reductions and also keeping things in shared memory and using wider locals by using block clusters instead of just blocks
3. More general PSO implementation that can be used for other problems (e.g. TSP, knapsack, etc.)
4. Add make tensor descriptors for more efficient memory access patterns
5. Add support for mixed precision (e.g. FP16) to further reduce memory bandwidth
6. Use gdc_wait to overlap the global best update and path recomputation with the local PSO updates
7. in the MC_kernels make some stuff static
8. swizzle the tensors to improve memory access patterns (e.g. use a tiled layout for the particles and their velocities)
9. get rid of the tensor descriptors and just use raw pointers to load particles

